CHAPTER 7.5 Entropy_Driven_Cellular_Automaton


##
HOT FIX


Kick Check ‚Äî Text Summary
Gaps
Specific heat peak ambiguity ‚Äî The audit flagged a ‚Äúfail‚Äù because the peak is broad and plateau‚Äëlike; no per‚Äësite normalization is shown in the figure.
No explicit uncertainty bands ‚Äî Observables are plotted as single lines; confidence intervals or error bars are absent.
Binder cumulant interpretation ‚Äî U_P(Œ≤) is mentioned but not contextualized against known universality class expectations.
ŒîS baseline rationale ‚Äî The choice of Œ≤_min as the entropy baseline is noted but not justified in‚Äëtext.

Conflicts
Audit vs. narrative ‚Äî The audit log calls the specific heat peak check a fail, but the caption language softens it (‚Äúbroad plateau observed‚Äù), which could confuse readers about severity.
Œ∏(Œ≤) monotonicity ‚Äî Audit says ‚Äúpass,‚Äù but no visual inset or derivative plot is provided to prove monotonicity.
Polyakov vs. specific heat diagnostics ‚Äî The text implies Polyakov susceptibility is the sharper diagnostic, but the run spec still treats specific heat as primary.

Suggested Updates / Fixes
Clarify audit severity ‚Äî Explicitly state that the ‚Äúfail‚Äù is a morphology mismatch, not a missing transition.
Add per‚Äësite normalization ‚Äî Include C(Œ≤)/V in the figure or table for direct comparability.
Add uncertainty bands ‚Äî Overlay ¬±œÉ or bootstrap CI shading on all observable plots.
Binder cumulant context ‚Äî Add a one‚Äëline note comparing U_P(Œ≤) shape to expected universality class.
Justify ŒîS baseline ‚Äî Briefly explain why Œ≤_min is the chosen reference point.
Visual proof of monotonicity ‚Äî Add an inset showing dŒ∏/dŒ≤ ‚â• 0 across the scan.

Kick Check ‚Äî YAML Breakdown

