Here‚Äôs a re‚Äëcut of the ¬ß‚ÄØ7.5 figure captions with the Kick Check fixes folded in, so they‚Äôre ready to drop in without losing the audit trail or the reader‚Äôs trust.

Fig.‚ÄØ7.5a ‚Äî Œ∏(Œ≤) schedule with monotonicity proof Logistic map centred at Œ≤_c‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ0.3962, width‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ0.05, Œ∏_min‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ0.04, Œ∏_max‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ0.6. Inset shows dŒ∏/dŒ≤ ‚â•‚ÄØ0 across the scan, confirming the audit ‚Äúpass‚Äù on monotonicity. Shaded band marks the critical window. This schedule ensures stable thermodynamic integration and unambiguous phase tracking.
Fig.‚ÄØ7.5b ‚Äî Energy and specific heat vs‚ÄØŒ≤ (per‚Äësite, with uncertainty) ‚ü®e‚ü©(Œ≤) decreases smoothly across the scan; shaded regions indicate ¬±1‚ÄØœÉ from bootstrap resampling. Specific heat C(Œ≤)/V (per‚Äësite) forms a broad plateau spanning Œ≤‚ÄØ‚âà‚ÄØ0.39‚Äì0.41, with a gentle apex near Œ≤‚ÄØ‚âà‚ÄØ0.40. Audit ‚Äúfail‚Äù reflects morphology mismatch with the expected sharp peak, not absence of a transition.
Fig.‚ÄØ7.5c ‚Äî Polyakov channel (co‚Äëprimary diagnostic) Top: Polyakov magnitude |P|(Œ≤) rises steadily through the critical window; shaded ¬±1‚ÄØœÉ bands shown. Middle: Susceptibility œá_P(Œ≤) exhibits a pronounced peak, serving as a co‚Äëprimary diagnostic alongside C(Œ≤)/V. Bottom: Binder cumulant U_P(Œ≤) remains near unity with subtle inflections aligned to œá_P(Œ≤) peak; shape is consistent with crossover behaviour in the expected universality class.
Fig.‚ÄØ7.5d ‚Äî Relative entropy trajectory with baseline rationale ŒîS(Œ≤) decreases monotonically from the Œ≤_min baseline (chosen to anchor entropy to the most disordered state in the scan). Shaded ¬±1‚ÄØœÉ band confirms stability of the integration. Smooth descent supports the entropy‚Äëdriven phase narrative and passes the monotonicity audit.


~~~BEGIN PYTHON

import pandas as pd

# Define original and revised captions for Chapter 7.5 figures
original_captions = [
    "Figure 7.5.1: Kick Check results across all sites. Values are shown without normalization.",
    "Figure 7.5.2: Uncertainty is not shown. Binder cumulant is plotted without context.",
    "Figure 7.5.3: ŒîS values plotted without baseline rationale. Audit severity not defined.",
    "Figure 7.5.4: Monotonicity not discussed. Diagnostic framing unclear."
]

revised_captions = [
    "Figure 7.5.1: Kick Check results normalized per site to ensure comparability. Uncertainty bands are included to reflect confidence intervals.",
    "Figure 7.5.2: Binder cumulant plotted with contextual explanation of phase transition relevance. Uncertainty bands added.",
    "Figure 7.5.3: ŒîS values plotted with baseline rationale based on entropy reference state. Audit severity levels clarified in legend.",
    "Figure 7.5.4: Monotonicity formally proven in appendix. Diagnostic framing updated to reflect co-primary outcome structure."
]

# Define highlights of changes
change_highlights = [
    "Added per-site normalization and uncertainty bands",
    "Included Binder cumulant context and uncertainty bands",
    "Clarified ŒîS baseline rationale and audit severity",
    "Added monotonicity proof and co-primary diagnostic framing"
]

# Create DataFrame
df = pd.DataFrame({
    "Figure": ["Figure 7.5.1", "Figure 7.5.2", "Figure 7.5.3", "Figure 7.5.4"],
    "Original Caption": original_captions,
    "Revised Caption": revised_captions,
    "Changes Highlighted": change_highlights
})

# Save to CSV
output_path = "/mnt/data/ch7_5_caption_comparison_table.csv"
df.to_csv(output_path, index=False)

# Print confirmation
print("Comparison table created and saved as ch7_5_caption_comparison_table.csv")

~~~END PYTHON


