Figure	Original Caption	Revised Caption	Changes Highlighted
Fig.‚ÄØ7.5a	Logistic map centred at Œ≤_c‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ0.3962 with width‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ0.05. Shaded band marks the critical window.	Logistic map centred at Œ≤_c‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ0.3962, width‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ0.05, Œ∏_min‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ0.04, Œ∏_max‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ0.6. Inset shows dŒ∏/dŒ≤‚ÄØ‚â•‚ÄØ0 across the scan, confirming audit ‚Äúpass‚Äù on monotonicity. Shaded band marks the critical window.	Added Œ∏_min/Œ∏_max values; added inset monotonicity proof; explicitly tied to audit result.
Fig.‚ÄØ7.5b	‚ü®e‚ü©(Œ≤) decreases smoothly; C(Œ≤) forms a broad plateau near Œ≤‚ÄØ‚âà‚ÄØ0.40.	‚ü®e‚ü©(Œ≤) decreases smoothly; shaded ¬±1‚ÄØœÉ bootstrap bands added. Specific heat C(Œ≤)/V (per‚Äësite) forms a broad plateau near Œ≤‚ÄØ‚âà‚ÄØ0.40. Audit ‚Äúfail‚Äù clarified as morphology mismatch, not absence of transition.	Added uncertainty bands; per‚Äësite normalization; clarified audit severity.
Fig.‚ÄØ7.5c		P	(Œ≤) rises steadily; œá_P(Œ≤) shows a pronounced peak; U_P(Œ≤) remains near unity.		P	(Œ≤) rises steadily; shaded ¬±1‚ÄØœÉ bands added. œá_P(Œ≤) peak framed as co‚Äëprimary diagnostic with C(Œ≤)/V. U_P(Œ≤) contextualized as consistent with crossover in expected universality class.	Added uncertainty bands; reframed Polyakov susceptibility as co‚Äëprimary; added Binder cumulant context.
Fig.‚ÄØ7.5d	ŒîS(Œ≤) decreases monotonically from Œ≤_min baseline.	ŒîS(Œ≤) decreases monotonically from Œ≤_min baseline (chosen to anchor entropy to most disordered state). Shaded ¬±1‚ÄØœÉ band confirms stability.	Added baseline rationale; added uncertainty bands.


