üîπ Near‚ÄëTerm Enhancements
Fail‚ÄëFast CI Diagnostics: ¬ß‚ÄØ10 tolerances (volume‚ÄØŒµ‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ0.005, curvature‚ÄØœÑ‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ0.001, monotonicity_order‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ4) are now wired into continuous integration. Any breach in curvature guard, order‚Äën monotonicity, or ŒîS‚ÄìŒîVol correlation halts a run. This bakes the baseline‚Äôs ‚Äúpass all gates‚Äù ethos into day‚Äëto‚Äëday work.

Correlation Scaling Study: New correlation_study block sweeps L‚ÄØ‚àà‚ÄØ{64,‚Ä¶,256} and K‚ÄØ‚àà‚ÄØ{2,3} with Pearson/Spearman ‚â•‚ÄØ0.8 logged. It extends the r‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ0.86, œÅ‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ0.84 baseline result into a finite‚Äësize scaling dataset.

Adaptive œÑ: Replaces fixed œÑ with a 95th‚Äëpercentile ensemble measure of |S‚Ä≥(Œ≤)| over seeds‚ÄØ[101,‚ÄØ202,‚ÄØ303], making curvature guarding responsive to the actual Œ≤‚Äëband landscape.

üîπ Mid‚ÄëTerm Trajectory
L,K‚ÄëSpecific Guard Fits: Add guard_polynomial_fitting that least‚Äësquares fits Œ≤‚Å¥‚ÄØ‚àí‚ÄØ3Œ≤¬≤‚ÄØ+‚ÄØ2 to each (L,K) pair‚Äôs S‚Ä≥(Œ≤) data. Results populate a lookup table for tailored stability gates.

A·µ¢‚±º Facets from Polytope Normals: Map facet normals from Delaunay geometry into interaction weights A·µ¢‚±º(t), tightening the entropy‚Äìgeometry correspondence and opening control hooks.

Phase‚ÄëTransition Presignals: Define geometric thresholds (e.g. |S‚Ä≤(Œ≤)|‚ÄØ>‚ÄØ0.5) to flag transitions before full evolution, logging them alongside ¬ß‚ÄØ10 geometry diagnostics to save compute.

üìà Impact
Reproducibility is safeguarded by CI‚Äëdriven quality control.

Scaling laws get a hard dataset rather than anecdotal trends.

Stability adapts dynamically via ensemble‚Äëbased œÑ and (L,K)‚Äëspecific guard polynomials.

