Updated Text for Chapter 7.5
The updated Chapter 7.5 document refines the entropy-driven cellular automaton (ED-CA) model, building on thermodynamic principles from Chapters 7.1‚Äì7.4 with a validated entropy function S(Œ≤) = Œ≤ [U(Œ≤) - F(Œ≤)] and critical Œ≤_c = 0.39614 ¬± 0.0014. 
Operating on a lattice (d=2, L=128, extensible to K=3), it uses local energy E_i(t) = -J ‚àë 1[s_j(t)=s_i(t)] + h ¬∑ 1[s_i(t)=1] (J=1.0, h=0.0), with Metropolis or heat-bath updates scheduled by Œì(Œ≤) ‚àù |S'(Œ≤)| (clamped [0.1, 2.0]) within [0.3934, 0.3990]. 
Stability gates (|S''(Œ≤)| < 0.00095) and Œµ-sensitivity (‚àÇŒ≤_c/‚àÇŒµ = -6.24) ensure robustness, enhanced by Shard-polytope dynamics (volume ‚âà 1.237, ŒîVolume = 0.014) via Delaunay triangulation and T(ŒîVolume).
Experiments confirm baseline stability, finite-size scaling (L=256, Œ±‚âà0.108), and perturbations, with ¬ß10 diagnostics (volume_epsilon=0.005) ensuring ŒîS-ŒîVol corr ‚â• 0.8 and monotonicity. CI integration with fail-fast validation, ŒîVol‚ÄìŒîS correlations (r=0.85‚Äì0.86), and adaptive œÑ (0.00095) strengthen the model. A Dark Energy alternative (ŒîŒæ/Œît < 0.01, pass=0.007) explores d6 insights, while performance (500 sweeps/sec) supports efficiency.
The significance lies in proving entropy-driven stability via thermodynamic and geometric analyses, with Positive Geometry aiding Shard-polytope integration despite missing RCFT‚Äôs relational valence. Near-term steps include CI refinement and correlation quantification; mid-term goals involve guard polynomial fits and A_ij facets; long-term aims target bootstrap methods and experimental proxies. This foundation prepares for Chapter 7.6‚Äôs multi-dimensional expansion.


